Description: Cisco Enterprise SIP firmware support for Asterisk chan_pjsip
 Ten shared modules that add Cisco Enterprise SIP firmware
 (7975 / 8841 / 8861 / 8865 …) compatibility to Asterisk's chan_pjsip
 channel driver, without patching Asterisk core.
 .
 Provides BLF Speed Dial line-button support, the Cisco RemoteCC
 optionsind/bulkupdate REGISTER flow that the firmware expects, server-
 pushed unsolicited Event: presence NOTIFYs, Cisco-flavoured PIDF body
 generation, DND/CFwdALL softkey handling, and CLI commands for
 service-control NOTIFYs (check-sync / restart / reset). Also adds Cisco
 call signaling headers/SDP quirks and handles initial Cisco RemoteCC REFER
 traffic, including HLog and MCID softkeys, plus Phase 1 conference
 control (read-only ConfList participant list).
 .
 Targets phones running Cisco's Enterprise SIP firmware which would
 otherwise need either CallManager or the cisco-usecallmanager chan_sip
 patch. This package supersedes that patch for sites running chan_pjsip.
